Welcome to Yoopta EditorThis is a full-featured example showcasing every plugin, mark, and UI component that Yoopta Editor offers. Type / anywhere to open the slash command menu, or use the floating toolbar to format text/Text FormattingYoopta supports rich text marks: bold, italic, underline, strikethrough, inline code, and highlighted text. You can combine them: bold + italic or all at once.Block TypesBlockquoteThe best way to predict the future is to invent it.CalloutCallout blocks are great for highlighting important information, tips, or warnings in your content.ListsBulleted, numbered, and to-do lists with nesting support:Drag and drop blocks to reorder content20+ block plugins available out of the boxFully extensible plugin architectureInstall with npm install @yoopta/editorAdd plugins you needRender the editor and start building[x] Try the slash command menu[ ] Drag blocks to reorder them[ ] Export to HTML or MarkdownCode BlocksSyntax-highlighted code blocks with language selection:import { createYooptaEditor } from '@yoopta/editor';
import Paragraph from '@yoopta/paragraph';

const plugins = [Paragraph];
const editor = createYooptaEditor({ plugins });

// Ready to build amazing editing experiences!Advanced BlocksTablesTables support adding/removing rows and columns, resizing, and rich text inside cells.ImageUpload images or paste a URL. Supports resizing, captions, and alignment.

        EmbedEmbed content from YouTube, Figma, CodeSandbox, Twitter, and more:Nested & Structured BlocksThese blocks have nested elements — multiple editable sections inside a single block.AccordionTabsStepsCode GroupTabbed code blocks — perfect for showing the same example in multiple languages:

